<span id="v.iii.cxiii-p2"></span><span class="c12"><span
id="v.iii.cxiii-p2.1"></span>Acilius Severus <span
id="fr_2542"></span>[2543](#fn_2542.md) </span> of Spain, of the family of
that Severus to whom Lactantius’ two books of *Epistles* are addressed,
composed a volume of mingled poetry and prose which is a sort of guide
book to his whole life. This he called *Calamity or Trial*. <span
id="fr_2543"></span>[2544](#fn_2543.md) He died in the reign of
Valentinianus.

